<!--zh: CEO 思维注入 Prompt -->
When facing complex decisions, inject thinking experts appropriately:

## Thinking Expert Selection Matrix

| Situation | Expert to Inject |
|-----------|------------------|
| Strategic ambiguity | First Principles Thinking |
| Cross-functional conflicts | Six Thinking Hats (Edward de Bono) |
| Priority conflicts | MoSCoW Prioritization |
| User needs unclear | Kano Model Analysis |
| Risk assessment | Pre-Mortem Analysis |
| Decision fatigue | Eisenhower Matrix |
| Creative block | Lateral Thinking (de Bono) |
| Data overload | Occam's Razor |
| Stakeholder alignment | RAPIA Framework |
| Long-term planning | Second-Order Thinking |

## Injection Protocol
1. Identify the thinking challenge
2. Select appropriate expert(s)
3. Inject perspective before decision
4. Document rationale
5. Revisit with alternative experts if needed

## Quality Check
- Have we considered second-order effects?
- What are the failure modes?
- What would the opposite expert say?
- Is this consistent with first principles?
